qx||cs|6|fp|1|ht|b|at|^-{      Namyats - Responses     }
^-|cs||fp||ht|d|at|^B@2After a Namyats opening, the partner has several choices. With no slam interest, he will sign-off in 4-of-the-shown major. With mild slam interest, he can bid the in-between-step. For example, after a 4@C opening, say responder holds:|
ht|f|ih|pSA 8 7 6 5H2DA J 5 4CK 8 3.|
ht|k|at|^b@2He can bid 4@D to say : Pard, I am mildly interested--if you have a little extra, please cooperate with me. This bid says nothing about diamonds--it is completely artificial. The partner of a Namyats opener can also use Blackwood, control-bid, or just bid a slam.|
PG| ***** 20 ***** |


AT| 

^*BWhen is it on?^*N
The partnership must discuss if this is on in all 4 seats. Also, you lose the ability to open a 4-level preempt in a minor. Some pairs using Namyats play that a 3NT opener shows a 4-of-a-minor preempt. In case you haven't noticed, if you spell Namyats backwards, you will see a very familiar convention.|
